00:33:08.740 --> 00:33:10.960 align:middle line:84%
They're being interrupted
by announcements and bells.

00:33:10.960 --> 00:33:13.674 align:middle line:84%
They're being told when to
stand up and sit down and go out

00:33:13.674 --> 00:33:15.340 align:middle line:84%
the hall and everything,
and they're not

00:33:15.340 --> 00:33:18.849 align:middle line:84%
able to sit and develop their
thinking or make something.

00:33:18.849 --> 00:33:20.140 align:middle line:90%
Oh, you have to stop right now.

00:33:20.140 --> 00:33:21.570 align:middle line:90%
Oh, you have to start right now.

00:33:21.570 --> 00:33:23.490 align:middle line:90%
None of that's natural.

00:33:23.490 --> 00:33:26.250 align:middle line:84%
But there's an awful lot
more homeschooling going on.

00:33:26.250 --> 00:33:27.200 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:33:27.200 --> 00:33:29.570 align:middle line:84%
And some people are doing
it to avoid inoculations

00:33:29.570 --> 00:33:31.170 align:middle line:84%
and other things, for
example, although they're

00:33:31.170 --> 00:33:33.753 align:middle line:84%
kind of tightening the noose on
that one in the United States.

00:33:33.753 --> 00:33:36.480 align:middle line:84%
But let's talk about the
whole notion of the fact

00:33:36.480 --> 00:33:38.530 align:middle line:84%
that children
themselves are changing.

00:33:38.530 --> 00:33:41.550 align:middle line:84%
It's a different kind of being
that's coming onto the planet

00:33:41.550 --> 00:33:42.050 align:middle line:90%
now.

00:33:42.050 --> 00:33:43.466 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: Well,
and you know what

00:33:43.466 --> 00:33:46.010 align:middle line:84%
happens to those kinds of beings
that are, perhaps, coming in

00:33:46.010 --> 00:33:49.880 align:middle line:84%
with more senses, more
connectivity, more

00:33:49.880 --> 00:33:52.960 align:middle line:84%
intuition, and seeing
right through people.

00:33:52.960 --> 00:33:54.760 align:middle line:84%
They can tell when
people are lying.

00:33:54.760 --> 00:33:55.760 align:middle line:90%
What do we do with them?

00:33:55.760 --> 00:33:56.490 align:middle line:90%
Medicate them.

00:33:56.490 --> 00:33:57.520 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Medicate them.

00:33:57.520 --> 00:33:58.021 align:middle line:90%
Ritalin.

00:33:58.021 --> 00:33:59.895 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: And then
they're hooked on these--

00:33:59.895 --> 00:34:01.089 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Methamphetamines.

00:34:01.089 --> 00:34:02.630 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: They're
hooked after that,

00:34:02.630 --> 00:34:05.130 align:middle line:84%
and their lives are practically
ruined, as far as I can see.

00:34:05.130 --> 00:34:06.620 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Talk about that cycle.

00:34:06.620 --> 00:34:08.460 align:middle line:90%
What happens to those kids?

00:34:08.460 --> 00:34:11.692 align:middle line:84%
They can't keep them on
after the age of 18, right?

00:34:11.692 --> 00:34:12.650 align:middle line:90%
Is that when that ends?

00:34:12.650 --> 00:34:14.010 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: Well, what they
do is they transfer it

00:34:14.010 --> 00:34:15.020 align:middle line:90%
into antidepressants.

00:34:15.020 --> 00:34:15.939 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:34:15.939 --> 00:34:18.570 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: SSRIs
are so dangerous.

00:34:18.570 --> 00:34:19.630 align:middle line:90%
It blows my mind.

00:34:19.630 --> 00:34:21.269 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Explan what SSRIs are.

00:34:21.269 --> 00:34:23.060 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: Well, that's
what is the essence

00:34:23.060 --> 00:34:24.330 align:middle line:90%
of an antidepressant is.

00:34:24.330 --> 00:34:27.790 align:middle line:84%
And what it's doing is it's
stimulating parts of the brain

00:34:27.790 --> 00:34:30.000 align:middle line:84%
and suppressing
parts of the brain.

00:34:30.000 --> 00:34:32.860 align:middle line:84%
And so there's been interviews
with psychiatrists saying,

00:34:32.860 --> 00:34:34.750 align:middle line:84%
well, how young can you
put a child on SSRIs?

00:34:34.750 --> 00:34:37.000 align:middle line:84%
And they're interviewing
them, and they're saying, oh,

00:34:37.000 --> 00:34:38.440 align:middle line:90%
13, 10, 8.

00:34:38.440 --> 00:34:40.949 align:middle line:90%
And the next guy, 6 months.

00:34:40.949 --> 00:34:41.745 align:middle line:90%
In the womb.

00:34:41.745 --> 00:34:42.803 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Ugh.

00:34:42.803 --> 00:34:44.969 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: But the thing
is, you can't get off them.

00:34:44.969 --> 00:34:45.968 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: No, you can't.

00:34:45.968 --> 00:34:46.677 align:middle line:90%
They're addicted.

00:34:46.677 --> 00:34:48.343 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: I'll tell
you something else.

00:34:48.343 --> 00:34:50.600 align:middle line:84%
I spoke to you about
measuring consciousness fields

00:34:50.600 --> 00:34:52.439 align:middle line:90%
and this device that I have.

00:34:52.439 --> 00:34:54.980 align:middle line:84%
There's a stipulation that if
somebody is on antidepressants,

00:34:54.980 --> 00:34:56.812 align:middle line:90%
the machine won't work.

00:34:56.812 --> 00:34:57.520 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Really?

00:34:57.520 --> 00:34:58.710 align:middle line:90%
Now, OK.

00:34:58.710 --> 00:35:00.102 align:middle line:90%
That was in our last interview.

00:35:00.102 --> 00:35:01.560 align:middle line:84%
Talk about the
machine a little bit

00:35:01.560 --> 00:35:03.891 align:middle line:84%
and explain the profundity
of what you've just said.

00:35:03.891 --> 00:35:05.390 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: What the
machine is doing

00:35:05.390 --> 00:35:08.930 align:middle line:84%
is you insert your fingertips
onto a photographic plate.

00:35:08.930 --> 00:35:11.750 align:middle line:84%
A small impulse comes up, and it
measures the photonic emissions

00:35:11.750 --> 00:35:14.840 align:middle line:84%
around your fingers, which
are connected to the nerve

00:35:14.840 --> 00:35:16.930 align:middle line:84%
endings and the end
of the meridians.

00:35:16.930 --> 00:35:19.790 align:middle line:84%
That's logarithmically
recalculated around the body,

00:35:19.790 --> 00:35:21.710 align:middle line:84%
and then you can see
the overall health

00:35:21.710 --> 00:35:25.514 align:middle line:84%
of the person and the emotional
spiritual activity going.

00:35:25.514 --> 00:35:26.680 align:middle line:90%
And it's extremely accurate.

00:35:26.680 --> 00:35:29.330 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I've studied
this for a long time.

00:35:29.330 --> 00:35:33.420 align:middle line:84%
And so when a person
is on antidepressants,

00:35:33.420 --> 00:35:36.150 align:middle line:84%
it's like their auric
field is deadened.

00:35:36.150 --> 00:35:37.764 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Interesting.

00:35:37.764 --> 00:35:39.430 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: But, you
can't come off them.

00:35:39.430 --> 00:35:43.070 align:middle line:84%
If you're on them for 5 years,
it takes 2 and 1/2 years

00:35:43.070 --> 00:35:44.390 align:middle line:90%
to wean yourself off them.

00:35:44.390 --> 00:35:47.101 align:middle line:84%
But all the problems
that you had-- let's say

00:35:47.101 --> 00:35:47.850 align:middle line:90%
you were agitated.

00:35:47.850 --> 00:35:50.735 align:middle line:84%
Let's say you had
some kind of fear

00:35:50.735 --> 00:35:53.430 align:middle line:90%
or pain or psychological stress.

00:35:53.430 --> 00:35:56.410 align:middle line:84%
When you get off them, you've
got that same fear, pain,

00:35:56.410 --> 00:35:59.335 align:middle line:84%
and psychological stress, but
you become less productive.

00:35:59.335 --> 00:36:02.290 align:middle line:84%
And the number of
people that are on them

00:36:02.290 --> 00:36:03.710 align:middle line:90%
is absolutely staggering.

00:36:03.710 --> 00:36:05.840 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: What are
the numbers now?

00:36:05.840 --> 00:36:08.910 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: 60% of all
adults, and counting.

00:36:08.910 --> 00:36:09.890 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Whoa, whoa.

00:36:09.890 --> 00:36:13.410 align:middle line:84%
60% are on some kind
of antidepressant?

00:36:13.410 --> 00:36:15.390 align:middle line:90%
>>BOULTER: Yes.

00:36:15.390 --> 00:36:17.690 align:middle line:90%
That's a fact.

00:36:17.690 --> 00:36:18.945 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I had no idea.

00:36:18.945 --> 00:36:19.570 align:middle line:90%
>>BOULTER: Yep.

00:36:19.570 --> 00:36:20.830 align:middle line:90%
That's frightening.

00:36:20.830 --> 00:36:22.080 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That is frightening.

00:36:22.080 --> 00:36:23.000 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: It's
completely frightening.

00:36:23.000 --> 00:36:24.310 align:middle line:90%
And you know what?

00:36:24.310 --> 00:36:26.600 align:middle line:84%
They're addictive,
and so the physicians

00:36:26.600 --> 00:36:28.940 align:middle line:84%
and the psychiatrists
make money forever.

00:36:28.940 --> 00:36:32.320 align:middle line:84%
It's the way they used to
spend $2,000 in advertising

00:36:32.320 --> 00:36:33.990 align:middle line:84%
for every smoker,
because they knew

00:36:33.990 --> 00:36:35.627 align:middle line:84%
they would smoke for
their whole life.

00:36:35.627 --> 00:36:37.960 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But, you know, it
does something else as well.

00:36:37.960 --> 00:36:40.980 align:middle line:84%
If the parent has already
taken this on board

00:36:40.980 --> 00:36:42.880 align:middle line:84%
and deemed it to
be a reasonable way

00:36:42.880 --> 00:36:46.290 align:middle line:84%
to manage their own
emotions and so forth,

00:36:46.290 --> 00:36:48.500 align:middle line:84%
then it's really
a very short step

00:36:48.500 --> 00:36:50.405 align:middle line:90%
to do the same for your child.

00:36:50.405 --> 00:36:51.030 align:middle line:90%
>>BOULTER: Yes.

00:36:51.030 --> 00:36:54.900 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It becomes your family
culture, going to the therapist

00:36:54.900 --> 00:36:56.783 align:middle line:90%
and taking antidepressants.

00:36:56.783 --> 00:36:57.710 align:middle line:90%
>>BOULTER: Yes.

00:36:57.710 --> 00:36:58.570 align:middle line:90%
It's horrifying.

00:36:58.570 --> 00:36:59.695 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It is horrifying.

00:36:59.695 --> 00:37:03.140 align:middle line:84%
It makes me very sad to think
that so many of these really

00:37:03.140 --> 00:37:05.170 align:middle line:84%
beautiful young kids
that are being born

00:37:05.170 --> 00:37:10.015 align:middle line:84%
onto the planet at this time are
being drugged because they have

00:37:10.015 --> 00:37:11.580 align:middle line:84%
ants in their
pants, or they can't

00:37:11.580 --> 00:37:14.407 align:middle line:84%
sit for this kind of
garbage that we're

00:37:14.407 --> 00:37:16.490 align:middle line:84%
trying to stuff into their
little brains when they

00:37:16.490 --> 00:37:18.500 align:middle line:84%
want to be expressing
themselves.

00:37:18.500 --> 00:37:21.770 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: Why should they sit
in a closed-- I say closed air,

00:37:21.770 --> 00:37:25.560 align:middle line:84%
closed brain circulation system,
when they need to be outside?

00:37:25.560 --> 00:37:27.420 align:middle line:84%
Why can't they be doing
something creative?

00:37:27.420 --> 00:37:28.350 align:middle line:90%
But you know why?

00:37:28.350 --> 00:37:30.800 align:middle line:84%
The reason is it's
harder to manage.

00:37:30.800 --> 00:37:33.720 align:middle line:84%
If you've got one teacher, and
you've got 60 children, 40, 30,

00:37:33.720 --> 00:37:36.490 align:middle line:84%
20, however the
schools are organized,

00:37:36.490 --> 00:37:40.519 align:middle line:84%
basically, it's a
position of control.

00:37:40.519 --> 00:37:41.060 align:middle line:90%
I'm the boss.

00:37:41.060 --> 00:37:41.710 align:middle line:90%
You sit down.

00:37:41.710 --> 00:37:43.810 align:middle line:84%
Well, that's-- what's
that training us for.

00:37:43.810 --> 00:37:48.200 align:middle line:84%
That's training us to be in a
society that's controlling us.

00:37:48.200 --> 00:37:50.800 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So now what we
have to do-- our generation

00:37:50.800 --> 00:37:52.405 align:middle line:84%
and the next
generation down who's

00:37:52.405 --> 00:37:55.210 align:middle line:84%
now making these decisions
for their little kids--

00:37:55.210 --> 00:37:59.160 align:middle line:84%
their young children-- we have
been brainwashed into thinking

00:37:59.160 --> 00:38:01.250 align:middle line:84%
that we all need
a college degree.

00:38:01.250 --> 00:38:05.440 align:middle line:84%
We have to get-- Egoically,
we have to get off of that,

00:38:05.440 --> 00:38:07.400 align:middle line:84%
and to give permission
to the children

00:38:07.400 --> 00:38:10.190 align:middle line:84%
to go in these new directions
that you're talking about.

00:38:10.190 --> 00:38:12.490 align:middle line:90%
It really starts with us.

00:38:12.490 --> 00:38:14.310 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: Well, I
say we can surpass

00:38:14.310 --> 00:38:15.890 align:middle line:84%
what you get in
a college degree.

00:38:15.890 --> 00:38:17.140 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Let's talk about it.

00:38:17.140 --> 00:38:21.410 align:middle line:84%
Let's get into the-- what a
college degree-- not a coll--

00:38:21.410 --> 00:38:23.700 align:middle line:84%
a college edu--
what an education,

00:38:23.700 --> 00:38:28.040 align:middle line:84%
a holistic education, would look
like at any level in your life

00:38:28.040 --> 00:38:31.780 align:middle line:84%
through the internet based
platforms you're talking about.

00:38:31.780 --> 00:38:34.730 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: Well, first of all,
an 8-year-old or a 70-year-old

00:38:34.730 --> 00:38:37.970 align:middle line:84%
could be in the same course, and
they can operate at the level

00:38:37.970 --> 00:38:40.690 align:middle line:90%
that they choose to.

00:38:40.690 --> 00:38:42.220 align:middle line:90%
It's a whole different paradigm.

00:38:42.220 --> 00:38:45.480 align:middle line:84%
But what is important to
me is cross disciplinary.

00:38:45.480 --> 00:38:50.350 align:middle line:84%
So I talk about culturally
inclusive, multimedia,

00:38:50.350 --> 00:38:53.410 align:middle line:90%
interactive, online curriculum.

00:38:53.410 --> 00:38:54.400 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:38:54.400 --> 00:38:58.200 align:middle line:84%
And teaching academic writing,
teaching research skills,

00:38:58.200 --> 00:38:59.720 align:middle line:90%
even to a kid.

00:38:59.720 --> 00:39:00.760 align:middle line:90%
How you collect data.

00:39:00.760 --> 00:39:01.950 align:middle line:90%
All these different things.

00:39:01.950 --> 00:39:06.100 align:middle line:84%
And then to go out in a
multi-disciplinary setting

00:39:06.100 --> 00:39:08.870 align:middle line:84%
and come up with a hypothesis
and do some testing.

00:39:08.870 --> 00:39:11.189 align:middle line:90%
Film something.

00:39:11.189 --> 00:39:12.480 align:middle line:90%
Look at the progress of people.

00:39:12.480 --> 00:39:14.500 align:middle line:84%
So there's character
development.

00:39:14.500 --> 00:39:17.650 align:middle line:84%
I always like a movie that's
got good character development.

00:39:17.650 --> 00:39:18.850 align:middle line:90%
So where do you see that?

00:39:18.850 --> 00:39:21.480 align:middle line:84%
And so there's different
ways to structure courses

00:39:21.480 --> 00:39:25.310 align:middle line:84%
that allows for students to be
using a multiplicity of skills

00:39:25.310 --> 00:39:27.770 align:middle line:84%
that they develop
in every course.

00:39:27.770 --> 00:39:30.350 align:middle line:84%
Now, I also think there needs
to be parallel structure.

00:39:30.350 --> 00:39:33.849 align:middle line:84%
So across the board,
in an environment--

00:39:33.849 --> 00:39:35.140 align:middle line:90%
an online learning environment.

00:39:35.140 --> 00:39:38.410 align:middle line:84%
You can't be asking different
things in different courses.

00:39:38.410 --> 00:39:40.080 align:middle line:90%
This is the format we're using.

00:39:40.080 --> 00:39:42.380 align:middle line:84%
This is the program
we use for this.

00:39:42.380 --> 00:39:43.860 align:middle line:90%
And everything is the same.

00:39:43.860 --> 00:39:46.980 align:middle line:84%
So as they move between
courses, they take their skills

00:39:46.980 --> 00:39:48.790 align:middle line:84%
with them, and they
develop on those.

00:39:48.790 --> 00:39:50.980 align:middle line:84%
And they can even take
their project with them

00:39:50.980 --> 00:39:52.450 align:middle line:90%
and make it more colorful.

00:39:52.450 --> 00:39:54.040 align:middle line:84%
So instead of having
still pictures,

00:39:54.040 --> 00:39:55.999 align:middle line:84%
they put in little video
clips or something.

00:39:55.999 --> 00:39:58.540 align:middle line:84%
And they just keep on making it
better and better and better.

00:39:58.540 --> 00:40:01.060 align:middle line:84%
Well, I've seen this
in action, because I've

00:40:01.060 --> 00:40:03.050 align:middle line:90%
taught this way for a long time.

00:40:03.050 --> 00:40:05.850 align:middle line:84%
And they told me I could
only give one A plus.

00:40:05.850 --> 00:40:11.750 align:middle line:84%
Well, if I have 12 students that
are absolutely dazzling that

00:40:11.750 --> 00:40:14.830 align:middle line:84%
are creating things that
are better than I created,

00:40:14.830 --> 00:40:17.264 align:middle line:84%
I don't see why I can't
give them all an A plus.

00:40:17.264 --> 00:40:19.680 align:middle line:84%
But then these students turn
around and they can teach it.

00:40:19.680 --> 00:40:21.499 align:middle line:84%
So it's just this
incredible environment.

00:40:21.499 --> 00:40:24.040 align:middle line:84%
The other thing is if you can
post examples of other people's

00:40:24.040 --> 00:40:26.360 align:middle line:90%
work, everybody does better.

00:40:26.360 --> 00:40:29.250 align:middle line:84%
And then next semester,
they do better than that.

00:40:29.250 --> 00:40:32.490 align:middle line:84%
So you've got these
people who are filmmakers,

00:40:32.490 --> 00:40:35.710 align:middle line:84%
who are musicians, who are
recording what they can do,

00:40:35.710 --> 00:40:38.980 align:middle line:84%
and it's incredible, because
you give them something

00:40:38.980 --> 00:40:40.500 align:middle line:90%
that they can take away.

00:40:40.500 --> 00:40:42.811 align:middle line:84%
So in Taiwan, when I was
teaching at the college,

00:40:42.811 --> 00:40:44.060 align:middle line:90%
these students couldn't write.

00:40:44.060 --> 00:40:45.100 align:middle line:90%
They couldn't do anything.

00:40:45.100 --> 00:40:46.880 align:middle line:84%
And the other thing is
that I'm on their team,

00:40:46.880 --> 00:40:48.600 align:middle line:84%
so they would hand
me a one page essay

00:40:48.600 --> 00:40:50.359 align:middle line:90%
that would have 50 mistakes.

00:40:50.359 --> 00:40:51.900 align:middle line:84%
I would correct
every single mistake,

00:40:51.900 --> 00:40:53.524 align:middle line:84%
and I would ask them
to write it again.

00:40:53.524 --> 00:40:55.522 align:middle line:84%
And it would come back
to me with 30 mistakes.

00:40:55.522 --> 00:40:56.730 align:middle line:90%
And I corrected it all again.

00:40:56.730 --> 00:40:58.750 align:middle line:84%
And all of a sudden,
they're like, oh.

00:40:58.750 --> 00:41:02.060 align:middle line:84%
She gave me the answer, and
I wasn't paying attention.

00:41:02.060 --> 00:41:03.820 align:middle line:90%
Because they're asleep.

00:41:03.820 --> 00:41:06.096 align:middle line:84%
They don't even know
how to pay attention.

00:41:06.096 --> 00:41:07.470 align:middle line:84%
After that, they
know it probably

00:41:07.470 --> 00:41:10.010 align:middle line:90%
took me an hour to mark these.

00:41:10.010 --> 00:41:11.800 align:middle line:84%
And then they
carefully write it out,

00:41:11.800 --> 00:41:14.594 align:middle line:84%
and they decorate it and
put it into a format,

00:41:14.594 --> 00:41:15.760 align:middle line:90%
and then they give it to me.

00:41:15.760 --> 00:41:16.920 align:middle line:90%
And they do 10 of these.

00:41:16.920 --> 00:41:20.170 align:middle line:84%
Well, then I give them back
a book of their writing

00:41:20.170 --> 00:41:21.660 align:middle line:90%
that's perfect.

00:41:21.660 --> 00:41:24.300 align:middle line:90%
Well, you're looking at that.

00:41:24.300 --> 00:41:26.379 align:middle line:84%
They try to say, well,
I still can't write.

00:41:26.379 --> 00:41:27.170 align:middle line:90%
But they've got it.

00:41:27.170 --> 00:41:27.520 align:middle line:90%
>>BOULTER: But they've done it.

00:41:27.520 --> 00:41:27.925 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:41:27.925 --> 00:41:29.610 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: They've done it,
and they did it themselves.

00:41:29.610 --> 00:41:31.776 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And you've given
them not only validation,

00:41:31.776 --> 00:41:33.590 align:middle line:84%
but through this
process, and the process

00:41:33.590 --> 00:41:35.548 align:middle line:84%
you were talking about
earlier with these kids,

00:41:35.548 --> 00:41:37.800 align:middle line:84%
because they've selected
what they're studying,

00:41:37.800 --> 00:41:40.030 align:middle line:84%
this means there's meaning
to what they're doing.

00:41:40.030 --> 00:41:42.390 align:middle line:84%
There's purpose to
what they're doing.

00:41:42.390 --> 00:41:44.180 align:middle line:84%
And this is something
I know-- and there's

00:41:44.180 --> 00:41:45.479 align:middle line:90%
a wonderful little film.

00:41:45.479 --> 00:41:46.770 align:middle line:90%
I don't know if you've seen it.

00:41:46.770 --> 00:41:48.950 align:middle line:90%
RSA Animate Film.

00:41:48.950 --> 00:41:53.950 align:middle line:84%
It's about changing education
by Sir Ken Robinson.

00:41:53.950 --> 00:41:56.230 align:middle line:84%
And if you have a chance,
by the way, anybody,

00:41:56.230 --> 00:41:59.490 align:middle line:84%
try to find that RSA Animate,
Sir Ken Robinson, on education

00:41:59.490 --> 00:41:59.990 align:middle line:90%
on YouTube.

00:41:59.990 --> 00:42:01.400 align:middle line:90%
It's a great little film.

00:42:01.400 --> 00:42:05.530 align:middle line:10%
And toward the end, it says,
what came out of all this?

00:42:05.530 --> 00:42:08.530 align:middle line:84%
The real understanding in
research is you have to--

00:42:08.530 --> 00:42:10.560 align:middle line:84%
and this is for
workers, for kids--

00:42:10.560 --> 00:42:12.630 align:middle line:84%
there has to be
meaning and purpose.

00:42:12.630 --> 00:42:16.170 align:middle line:84%
The system now completely
lacks meaning and purpose.

00:42:16.170 --> 00:42:18.420 align:middle line:84%
So you're giving
anyone-- doesn't matter

00:42:18.420 --> 00:42:21.520 align:middle line:84%
what their area of
interest is-- education

00:42:21.520 --> 00:42:24.670 align:middle line:84%
becomes meaningful and
purposeful to them.

00:42:24.670 --> 00:42:27.130 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: But an
opportunity for success.

00:42:27.130 --> 00:42:29.280 align:middle line:84%
So translating from
these students who

00:42:29.280 --> 00:42:31.820 align:middle line:84%
are learning English into
a university setting, what

00:42:31.820 --> 00:42:34.635 align:middle line:84%
I would do is somebody
would write a paper,

00:42:34.635 --> 00:42:36.010 align:middle line:84%
and I would
highlight where there

00:42:36.010 --> 00:42:39.690 align:middle line:84%
was a mistake in formatting
and academic writing style.

00:42:39.690 --> 00:42:42.040 align:middle line:84%
And then I'd put
a flag with a link

00:42:42.040 --> 00:42:44.730 align:middle line:84%
to a video tutorial that
gives the answer of what

00:42:44.730 --> 00:42:46.560 align:middle line:84%
the problem is,
that gives a lesson.

00:42:46.560 --> 00:42:48.880 align:middle line:84%
So they'd have all these
flags, and at first they'd

00:42:48.880 --> 00:42:50.870 align:middle line:84%
look at their paper and
maybe be overwhelmed.

00:42:50.870 --> 00:42:53.570 align:middle line:84%
But the real learning
in the whole course

00:42:53.570 --> 00:42:55.620 align:middle line:84%
is the amount of time
it takes to go through.

00:42:55.620 --> 00:42:57.500 align:middle line:84%
And it would take
them as long as it

00:42:57.500 --> 00:43:00.600 align:middle line:84%
would take me to write
it-- to correct it.

00:43:00.600 --> 00:43:03.600 align:middle line:84%
But if there was something
that I didn't have a flag for,

00:43:03.600 --> 00:43:06.290 align:middle line:84%
I would take time and
make a video tutorial.

00:43:06.290 --> 00:43:10.710 align:middle line:84%
And so even with questions
that somebody emailed me,

00:43:10.710 --> 00:43:12.630 align:middle line:84%
if it was a good question,
I could spend a day

00:43:12.630 --> 00:43:15.360 align:middle line:84%
answering that question,
making video tutorials

00:43:15.360 --> 00:43:16.352 align:middle line:90%
and making scaffolding.

00:43:16.352 --> 00:43:18.560 align:middle line:84%
Because what's happening if
somebody has a question--

00:43:18.560 --> 00:43:20.540 align:middle line:84%
I say they're
missing scaffolding.

00:43:20.540 --> 00:43:25.660 align:middle line:84%
They don't have the branch
to put the answer on.

00:43:25.660 --> 00:43:29.170 align:middle line:84%
And so then I always ask them
to post to Q and A with Dr. B.

00:43:29.170 --> 00:43:31.650 align:middle line:84%
And so I say, before
you ask me a question,

00:43:31.650 --> 00:43:33.931 align:middle line:84%
read Q and A with
Dr. B. And then

00:43:33.931 --> 00:43:36.180 align:middle line:84%
I started getting fewer and
fewer and fewer questions.

00:43:36.180 --> 00:43:39.380 align:middle line:84%
But if I got a question, I
could take the time to answer.

00:43:39.380 --> 00:43:41.680 align:middle line:84%
So this parallel
structure means that there

00:43:41.680 --> 00:43:47.450 align:middle line:84%
are resources-- banks of
resources-- for everything.

00:43:47.450 --> 00:43:49.720 align:middle line:84%
And the student takes
the time to go through it

00:43:49.720 --> 00:43:50.900 align:middle line:90%
at their own pace.

00:43:50.900 --> 00:43:53.940 align:middle line:84%
And if they get stumped,
I'm on their team,

00:43:53.940 --> 00:43:55.040 align:middle line:90%
and I can help them.

00:43:55.040 --> 00:43:58.060 align:middle line:84%
And if they have a question,
someone else has that question.

00:43:58.060 --> 00:44:01.770 align:middle line:84%
And so over time, you end up
with this incredible resource.

00:44:01.770 --> 00:44:04.000 align:middle line:84%
And then people become
more and more independent

00:44:04.000 --> 00:44:05.130 align:middle line:90%
and more efficient.

00:44:05.130 --> 00:44:08.420 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It just makes a lot
of sense in every respect.

00:44:08.420 --> 00:44:09.860 align:middle line:84%
But let's talk
about-- some people

00:44:09.860 --> 00:44:12.240 align:middle line:84%
may be listening right
now and thinking, yeah,

00:44:12.240 --> 00:44:14.475 align:middle line:84%
but what if you want
to become a doctor?

00:44:14.475 --> 00:44:16.520 align:middle line:84%
How are you going
to do that online?

00:44:16.520 --> 00:44:18.900 align:middle line:84%
Don't you still have to go
through the same process?

00:44:18.900 --> 00:44:21.760 align:middle line:84%
Don't you have to go through
the systems of higher education,

00:44:21.760 --> 00:44:24.676 align:middle line:84%
and then into your
residency, and on and on?

00:44:24.676 --> 00:44:26.050 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: Well,
I don't know who

00:44:26.050 --> 00:44:28.174 align:middle line:84%
would want to become a
doctor in this system that's

00:44:28.174 --> 00:44:29.330 align:middle line:90%
just a drug peddler.

00:44:29.330 --> 00:44:30.940 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well,
that's a second story.

00:44:30.940 --> 00:44:32.148 align:middle line:90%
>>BOULTER: But you know what?

00:44:32.148 --> 00:44:34.590 align:middle line:84%
If that's what they want
to do, that system exists.

00:44:34.590 --> 00:44:35.640 align:middle line:90%
That's the old system.

00:44:35.640 --> 00:44:35.970 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:44:35.970 --> 00:44:37.636 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: I don't
want to be creating--

00:44:37.636 --> 00:44:39.275 align:middle line:84%
I mean, if it supports
the old system,

00:44:39.275 --> 00:44:40.650 align:middle line:84%
I'm not exactly
interested in it.

00:44:40.650 --> 00:44:41.316 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:44:41.316 --> 00:44:44.295 align:middle line:84%
So basically, you're talking
about just saying, I unplug.

00:44:44.295 --> 00:44:45.880 align:middle line:90%
I'm unplugging from the system.

00:44:45.880 --> 00:44:47.980 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to make my own
way, create my own life,

00:44:47.980 --> 00:44:51.050 align:middle line:84%
create my own collaborations
and partnerships

00:44:51.050 --> 00:44:52.740 align:middle line:90%
and opportunities in the future.

00:44:52.740 --> 00:44:55.429 align:middle line:84%
I mean, if you start down that
road of self-responsibility,

00:44:55.429 --> 00:44:57.220 align:middle line:84%
you get to live that
the rest of your life,

00:44:57.220 --> 00:44:58.970 align:middle line:84%
but you have to
learn how to do that.

00:44:58.970 --> 00:45:01.530 align:middle line:84%
And those are the skills
we've yet to have been taught.

00:45:01.530 --> 00:45:04.580 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: And we've got
12 faculties and 42 courses

00:45:04.580 --> 00:45:08.450 align:middle line:84%
so far on Interactive U,
and it is about who are you?

00:45:08.450 --> 00:45:09.380 align:middle line:10%
What can you do?

00:45:09.380 --> 00:45:10.920 align:middle line:10%
How can you present yourself?

00:45:10.920 --> 00:45:13.045 align:middle line:10%
The other thing is you're
going to present yourself

00:45:13.045 --> 00:45:14.010 align:middle line:10%
to an employer.

00:45:14.010 --> 00:45:15.930 align:middle line:10%
Why do you stand apart?

00:45:15.930 --> 00:45:18.100 align:middle line:10%
And so there can be electronic
portfolios that say,

00:45:18.100 --> 00:45:20.130 align:middle line:10%
this person actually built this.

00:45:20.130 --> 00:45:21.840 align:middle line:84%
So as an employer,
would you rather

00:45:21.840 --> 00:45:24.829 align:middle line:84%
have somebody come in to say,
here's a diploma on website

00:45:24.829 --> 00:45:27.245 align:middle line:84%
building, or would you rather
have an electronic portfolio

00:45:27.245 --> 00:45:30.254 align:middle line:84%
to say, here's a website
this person built, right?

00:45:30.254 --> 00:45:30.920 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:45:30.920 --> 00:45:33.110 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: You tell me
which one is more useful.

00:45:33.110 --> 00:45:34.110 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:45:34.110 --> 00:45:36.290 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: And if a student
can conduct research,

00:45:36.290 --> 00:45:39.570 align:middle line:84%
can write academically, can
do all these different skills,

00:45:39.570 --> 00:45:43.770 align:middle line:84%
they understand cross
systems and all of this,

00:45:43.770 --> 00:45:44.904 align:middle line:90%
why wouldn't you hire them?

00:45:44.904 --> 00:45:45.570 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:45:45.570 --> 00:45:47.570 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: But the other thing
is if they don't hire you,

00:45:47.570 --> 00:45:49.361 align:middle line:84%
this person can stand
on their own two feet

00:45:49.361 --> 00:45:50.670 align:middle line:90%
and employ themselves.

00:45:50.670 --> 00:45:52.030 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That's the difference.

00:45:52.030 --> 00:45:54.937 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you really are creating
a type of self empowerment

00:45:54.937 --> 00:45:55.770 align:middle line:90%
through this system.

00:45:55.770 --> 00:45:56.770 align:middle line:90%
>>BOULTER: That's right.

00:45:56.770 --> 00:46:00.060 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: How do you speak
to the fears of the parents?

00:46:00.060 --> 00:46:02.030 align:middle line:84%
I want to go back to
that, because people

00:46:02.030 --> 00:46:03.170 align:middle line:90%
are listening right now.

00:46:03.170 --> 00:46:06.990 align:middle line:84%
They have their kid all lined up
to get them into whatever prep

00:46:06.990 --> 00:46:08.630 align:middle line:84%
school so that
they can get, just

00:46:08.630 --> 00:46:11.210 align:middle line:84%
like the opening of the
show, into the best college

00:46:11.210 --> 00:46:13.620 align:middle line:84%
and have the best opportunity
at graduate school.

00:46:13.620 --> 00:46:15.040 align:middle line:84%
How do you appeal
to their fears?

00:46:15.040 --> 00:46:18.265 align:middle line:84%
Because oftentimes, if they
were to query their own child,

00:46:18.265 --> 00:46:20.640 align:middle line:84%
they're not necessarily on
board with the parents' agenda

00:46:20.640 --> 00:46:21.149 align:middle line:90%
at all.

00:46:21.149 --> 00:46:22.440 align:middle line:90%
>>BOULTER: Well, you know what?

00:46:22.440 --> 00:46:24.731 align:middle line:84%
If the parents think the
students should go over there,

00:46:24.731 --> 00:46:25.744 align:middle line:90%
go.

00:46:25.744 --> 00:46:27.910 align:middle line:84%
I'm not trying to convince
anybody to come this way.

00:46:27.910 --> 00:46:30.740 align:middle line:84%
I'm picking up all the people
that got dropped in the ditch,

00:46:30.740 --> 00:46:31.546 align:middle line:90%
you know?

00:46:31.546 --> 00:46:35.670 align:middle line:84%
That it didn't work for, and
that don't need convincing.

00:46:35.670 --> 00:46:39.160 align:middle line:84%
Because there's a lot of people
that are interested in this.

00:46:39.160 --> 00:46:42.321 align:middle line:84%
So we'll leave it, like I
said, if the parents think

00:46:42.321 --> 00:46:44.820 align:middle line:84%
that the student's just going
to be sitting at the computer,

00:46:44.820 --> 00:46:47.399 align:middle line:84%
they don't realize
the use of technology.

00:46:47.399 --> 00:46:48.940 align:middle line:84%
I don't even know
how to answer that.

00:46:48.940 --> 00:46:50.640 align:middle line:90%
If they're afraid, go away.

00:46:50.640 --> 00:46:51.306 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:46:51.306 --> 00:46:52.430 align:middle line:90%
You're not talking to them.

00:46:52.430 --> 00:46:53.130 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: I'm not
talking to them.

00:46:53.130 --> 00:46:53.890 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK, very good.

00:46:53.890 --> 00:46:56.560 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: OK, let's talk a
little bit about Interactive U.

00:46:56.560 --> 00:47:00.940 align:middle line:84%
How it works, what the
breadth of subjects are,

00:47:00.940 --> 00:47:02.540 align:middle line:84%
and when it's going
to be available

00:47:02.540 --> 00:47:04.480 align:middle line:84%
and all of that for
a little bit here.

00:47:04.480 --> 00:47:06.310 align:middle line:84%
We have some time
to talk about it.

00:47:06.310 --> 00:47:07.480 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Thank you.

00:47:07.480 --> 00:47:09.710 align:middle line:84%
Well, I started working
on this about a year ago,

00:47:09.710 --> 00:47:13.455 align:middle line:84%
and I started the
first online course

00:47:13.455 --> 00:47:16.400 align:middle line:84%
that they had at this
university in Taiwan.

00:47:16.400 --> 00:47:18.320 align:middle line:84%
And I was working on an
international academic

00:47:18.320 --> 00:47:21.210 align:middle line:84%
cooperation project with
the Ministry of Education

00:47:21.210 --> 00:47:21.850 align:middle line:90%
in Taiwan.

00:47:21.850 --> 00:47:24.380 align:middle line:84%
And I actually worked on
three of those projects,

00:47:24.380 --> 00:47:25.810 align:middle line:90%
and I was project leader.

00:47:25.810 --> 00:47:29.490 align:middle line:84%
And so because I was developing
all these online courses,

00:47:29.490 --> 00:47:31.780 align:middle line:84%
I developed a
methodology for it.

00:47:31.780 --> 00:47:34.030 align:middle line:84%
But what I notice is
that the platforms

00:47:34.030 --> 00:47:36.770 align:middle line:84%
that they were using where
you could pay $10,000 a month

00:47:36.770 --> 00:47:41.800 align:middle line:84%
to use Blackboard or Elluminate
and those various coined

00:47:41.800 --> 00:47:44.472 align:middle line:84%
platforms were
actually inferior.

00:47:44.472 --> 00:47:45.680 align:middle line:90%
They weren't colorful enough.

00:47:45.680 --> 00:47:48.405 align:middle line:84%
I couldn't insert videos, I
couldn't use different colors,

00:47:48.405 --> 00:47:50.030 align:middle line:84%
because I always like
the courses to be

00:47:50.030 --> 00:47:52.720 align:middle line:84%
color coded, and
that sort of thing.

00:47:52.720 --> 00:47:56.150 align:middle line:90%
So I decided to build my own.

00:47:56.150 --> 00:48:00.530 align:middle line:84%
And so I worked with an
IT person from the UK,

00:48:00.530 --> 00:48:03.070 align:middle line:84%
and he actually had worked
for the UN for seven years

00:48:03.070 --> 00:48:04.760 align:middle line:90%
and the CIA for five years.

00:48:04.760 --> 00:48:05.930 align:middle line:90%
Brilliant guy.

00:48:05.930 --> 00:48:08.020 align:middle line:90%
And it was all about encryption.

00:48:08.020 --> 00:48:08.950 align:middle line:90%
Well, part of it.

00:48:08.950 --> 00:48:10.407 align:middle line:90%
That was what he understood.

00:48:10.407 --> 00:48:12.990 align:middle line:84%
Because I want to be able to do
streaming video that you can't

00:48:12.990 --> 00:48:16.260 align:middle line:84%
put it on YouTube, and to
keep something proprietary

00:48:16.260 --> 00:48:18.540 align:middle line:84%
within Interactive U that's
just for the students

00:48:18.540 --> 00:48:19.980 align:middle line:90%
that's useful to them.

00:48:19.980 --> 00:48:23.390 align:middle line:90%
And so we developed this system.

00:48:23.390 --> 00:48:25.140 align:middle line:84%
And so it's got all
the discussion boards.

00:48:25.140 --> 00:48:28.140 align:middle line:84%
It's got pages that are
like Facebook pages.

00:48:28.140 --> 00:48:30.890 align:middle line:84%
I'm renaming everything and
needing a new vocabulary

00:48:30.890 --> 00:48:32.390 align:middle line:84%
as we're getting
ready to launch.

00:48:32.390 --> 00:48:34.300 align:middle line:84%
But each student
will have the courses

00:48:34.300 --> 00:48:37.040 align:middle line:84%
they took, the
resources that they--

00:48:37.040 --> 00:48:39.200 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And it starts
at what age level?

00:48:39.200 --> 00:48:40.410 align:middle line:90%
>>BOULTER: I don't care.

00:48:40.410 --> 00:48:41.730 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Anyone who
can access a computer

00:48:41.730 --> 00:48:43.100 align:middle line:84%
and know how to
utilize a computer?

00:48:43.100 --> 00:48:43.480 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:48:43.480 --> 00:48:44.479 align:middle line:90%
>>BOULTER: No age limit.

00:48:44.479 --> 00:48:45.470 align:middle line:90%
You can be 8 or 80.

00:48:45.470 --> 00:48:48.329 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Can this become part
of a homeschooling program

00:48:48.329 --> 00:48:49.870 align:middle line:84%
as well, so it's
integrated that way?

00:48:49.870 --> 00:48:50.940 align:middle line:90%
>>BOULTER: And it's coordinated.

00:48:50.940 --> 00:48:53.115 align:middle line:84%
And actually, I wasn't
thinking about homeschooling

00:48:53.115 --> 00:48:53.740 align:middle line:90%
when I started.

00:48:53.740 --> 00:48:56.580 align:middle line:84%
I was thinking of an online
university and social action

00:48:56.580 --> 00:48:57.080 align:middle line:90%
network.

00:48:57.080 --> 00:48:58.860 align:middle line:84%
Online learning and
social action network.

00:48:58.860 --> 00:49:01.110 align:middle line:84%
But pretty much everybody I
mentioned it to said, what

00:49:01.110 --> 00:49:01.830 align:middle line:90%
about my kids?

00:49:01.830 --> 00:49:02.510 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:49:02.510 --> 00:49:03.968 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: And so
there's no reason

00:49:03.968 --> 00:49:07.070 align:middle line:84%
why that can't be from
K to 12 and all of that.

00:49:07.070 --> 00:49:08.875 align:middle line:84%
And so that's another
issue in terms

00:49:08.875 --> 00:49:11.000 align:middle line:84%
of whether they're going
to pass standardized tests

00:49:11.000 --> 00:49:13.250 align:middle line:84%
and try to get into the
system later and all of that.

00:49:13.250 --> 00:49:15.072 align:middle line:84%
And so this is
extremely complicated.

00:49:15.072 --> 00:49:16.530 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: These
are things that one

00:49:16.530 --> 00:49:17.821 align:middle line:90%
has to take into consideration.

00:49:17.821 --> 00:49:20.004 align:middle line:84%
You either go the new
path or you stay the old.

00:49:20.004 --> 00:49:21.545 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: But
they'll be consulting,

00:49:21.545 --> 00:49:23.462 align:middle line:84%
and there's ways that
you can learn that.

00:49:23.462 --> 00:49:24.420 align:middle line:90%
But back to the system.

00:49:24.420 --> 00:49:25.670 align:middle line:90%
Everybody will have their own.

00:49:25.670 --> 00:49:27.310 align:middle line:84%
It's Facebook meets
LinkedIn meets

00:49:27.310 --> 00:49:29.955 align:middle line:84%
iTunes meets YouTube in
an Interactive U context.

00:49:29.955 --> 00:49:30.580 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:49:30.580 --> 00:49:32.010 align:middle line:90%
Sounds like a fun school to me.

00:49:32.010 --> 00:49:32.935 align:middle line:90%
>>BOULTER: It sounds really fun.

00:49:32.935 --> 00:49:33.500 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:49:33.500 --> 00:49:35.537 align:middle line:84%
And so people are used
to that sort of thing.

00:49:35.537 --> 00:49:36.620 align:middle line:90%
So they can post pictures.

00:49:36.620 --> 00:49:37.828 align:middle line:90%
They can post their projects.

00:49:37.828 --> 00:49:39.150 align:middle line:90%
They can friend somebody.

00:49:39.150 --> 00:49:41.300 align:middle line:84%
So the important
thing to me-- it's

00:49:41.300 --> 00:49:44.640 align:middle line:84%
not just about learning and
information and knowledge.

00:49:44.640 --> 00:49:46.450 align:middle line:90%
It's about action.

00:49:46.450 --> 00:49:48.550 align:middle line:84%
Once you know something,
what are you going to do?

00:49:48.550 --> 00:49:50.890 align:middle line:84%
And so maybe there's going to
be projects-- third world--

00:49:50.890 --> 00:49:52.150 align:middle line:84%
projects in third
world countries

00:49:52.150 --> 00:49:53.941 align:middle line:84%
where they're getting
a stove for everyone,

00:49:53.941 --> 00:49:55.975 align:middle line:84%
or doing an
orphanage in Bolivia,

00:49:55.975 --> 00:49:57.350 align:middle line:84%
and there's people
on the ground.

00:49:57.350 --> 00:49:59.540 align:middle line:84%
It's all video driven, which
is what we're looking at.

00:49:59.540 --> 00:50:00.831 align:middle line:90%
Everybody's looking at YouTube.

00:50:00.831 --> 00:50:04.199 align:middle line:84%
Many people would prefer to do
YouTube than read, even now.

00:50:04.199 --> 00:50:05.740 align:middle line:84%
So if you can't beat
them, join them.

00:50:05.740 --> 00:50:07.770 align:middle line:84%
And so there's somebody on
the ground taking video down

00:50:07.770 --> 00:50:09.510 align:middle line:84%
in Bolivia, and
there's a team here,

00:50:09.510 --> 00:50:11.444 align:middle line:84%
and you friend
somebody that will--

00:50:11.444 --> 00:50:12.860 align:middle line:84%
and the social
action doesn't have

00:50:12.860 --> 00:50:14.443 align:middle line:84%
to be related to the
course you're in.

00:50:14.443 --> 00:50:17.850 align:middle line:84%
Just do something to help
everybody is the message.

00:50:17.850 --> 00:50:19.770 align:middle line:84%
Take the knowledge
you have and give,

00:50:19.770 --> 00:50:22.030 align:middle line:90%
and collaborate with someone.

00:50:22.030 --> 00:50:24.590 align:middle line:84%
And so that's where the
Facebook pages come in.

00:50:24.590 --> 00:50:25.940 align:middle line:90%
And reflective notes.

00:50:25.940 --> 00:50:28.280 align:middle line:84%
So when people watch
something or read something,

00:50:28.280 --> 00:50:29.030 align:middle line:90%
they don't own it.

00:50:29.030 --> 00:50:29.821 align:middle line:90%
They don't have it.

00:50:29.821 --> 00:50:32.476 align:middle line:84%
But they reflect on it, and they
learn more about themselves.

00:50:32.476 --> 00:50:34.350 align:middle line:84%
But then they can go
onto a discussion board,

00:50:34.350 --> 00:50:35.780 align:middle line:90%
discuss a certain piece.

00:50:35.780 --> 00:50:39.670 align:middle line:84%
And so everybody is learning and
sharing and growing and seeing

00:50:39.670 --> 00:50:41.340 align:middle line:90%
how to process.

00:50:41.340 --> 00:50:43.900 align:middle line:90%
This is the psychological thing.

00:50:43.900 --> 00:50:46.060 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: What about
the socialization of it?

00:50:46.060 --> 00:50:49.870 align:middle line:84%
I mean, how does that
part come together,

00:50:49.870 --> 00:50:52.580 align:middle line:84%
where people are connecting
with each other, as you would,

00:50:52.580 --> 00:50:54.870 align:middle line:84%
say, in a traditional
school environment?

00:50:54.870 --> 00:50:56.280 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: Well, in a
traditional school environment,

00:50:56.280 --> 00:50:57.850 align:middle line:84%
you're sitting in rows
not talking to anybody.

00:50:57.850 --> 00:50:59.290 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: No, I get that part.

00:50:59.290 --> 00:51:02.310 align:middle line:84%
But you can go and play a little
jump rope at recess or whatnot.

00:51:02.310 --> 00:51:03.932 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: OK, I
understand that.

00:51:03.932 --> 00:51:05.890 align:middle line:84%
So in various communities
where there's people,

00:51:05.890 --> 00:51:07.990 align:middle line:84%
they can get together
and do projects.

00:51:07.990 --> 00:51:11.400 align:middle line:84%
And so you can be outdoors
doing a project with somebody,

00:51:11.400 --> 00:51:12.660 align:middle line:90%
and somebody's filming it.

00:51:12.660 --> 00:51:14.340 align:middle line:84%
And then they upload
it and share it.

00:51:14.340 --> 00:51:15.190 align:middle line:84%
And so it doesn't
mean that you're

00:51:15.190 --> 00:51:16.790 align:middle line:90%
sitting at the computer all day.

00:51:16.790 --> 00:51:19.060 align:middle line:90%
And it is about interactivity.

00:51:19.060 --> 00:51:22.180 align:middle line:84%
But the thing is is
that we only just met,

00:51:22.180 --> 00:51:24.614 align:middle line:84%
but I've seen you on
video for all these years.

00:51:24.614 --> 00:51:25.280 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:51:25.280 --> 00:51:26.988 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: And so I
feel like I know you.

00:51:26.988 --> 00:51:29.110 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it's not that
different that there's

00:51:29.110 --> 00:51:30.410 align:middle line:90%
no screen in front.

00:51:30.410 --> 00:51:32.550 align:middle line:84%
And so I think that's
also a misnomer.

00:51:32.550 --> 00:51:34.800 align:middle line:84%
Like, when children go
away, and you've got Skype,

00:51:34.800 --> 00:51:37.500 align:middle line:84%
and you can see if they look
well, if they've got a haircut,

00:51:37.500 --> 00:51:38.640 align:middle line:90%
here's the dog.

00:51:38.640 --> 00:51:42.250 align:middle line:84%
With these kinds of things, we
really are able to communicate.

00:51:42.250 --> 00:51:44.720 align:middle line:84%
And so I've gone
for years working

00:51:44.720 --> 00:51:49.614 align:middle line:84%
with people, all kinds of
people that I've never met.

00:51:49.614 --> 00:51:51.780 align:middle line:84%
But that doesn't mean I
don't feel like I know them.

00:51:51.780 --> 00:51:53.350 align:middle line:84%
I know them by name,
I know their face,

00:51:53.350 --> 00:51:55.350 align:middle line:84%
I know their projects, I
know what they've done.

00:51:55.350 --> 00:51:57.560 align:middle line:84%
So it could be that you
meet people on the ground.

00:51:57.560 --> 00:51:59.430 align:middle line:84%
But when you're really
getting to work,

00:51:59.430 --> 00:52:02.111 align:middle line:90%
you can do that, collaborating.

00:52:02.111 --> 00:52:03.860 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And you can
do it through media.

00:52:03.860 --> 00:52:04.620 align:middle line:90%
>>BOULTER: Through media.

00:52:04.620 --> 00:52:05.745 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, absolutely.

00:52:05.745 --> 00:52:07.680 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: But you can
edit a paper together

00:52:07.680 --> 00:52:08.780 align:middle line:90%
on Skype in Google Docs.

00:52:08.780 --> 00:52:09.530 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:52:09.530 --> 00:52:11.230 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: These are the
skills that we teach people,

00:52:11.230 --> 00:52:12.714 align:middle line:84%
because we can say
hi and have tea,

00:52:12.714 --> 00:52:15.130 align:middle line:84%
but then we'll probably end
up sitting at our own computer

00:52:15.130 --> 00:52:16.190 align:middle line:90%
to do the work.

00:52:16.190 --> 00:52:17.950 align:middle line:84%
And so I think that
the interactivity

00:52:17.950 --> 00:52:19.360 align:middle line:90%
and the social part happens.

00:52:19.360 --> 00:52:20.930 align:middle line:90%
But people have friends.

00:52:20.930 --> 00:52:22.069 align:middle line:90%
They have neighbors.

00:52:22.069 --> 00:52:22.610 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

00:52:22.610 --> 00:52:24.320 align:middle line:84%
I just don't see
that as a problem.

00:52:24.320 --> 00:52:26.346 align:middle line:84%
But lots of people
bring these up as flags.

00:52:26.346 --> 00:52:28.720 align:middle line:84%
Well, you'll just be stuck
with a computer and that's it,

00:52:28.720 --> 00:52:29.845 align:middle line:90%
and you won't know anybody.

00:52:29.845 --> 00:52:31.249 align:middle line:84%
I don't think
that's the problem.

00:52:31.249 --> 00:52:32.790 align:middle line:84%
>>And Gerald Celente--
and he's good.

00:52:32.790 --> 00:52:34.130 align:middle line:90%
Gerald Celente is good.

00:52:34.130 --> 00:52:36.390 align:middle line:84%
I don't know what
his record is, but it

00:52:36.390 --> 00:52:40.640 align:middle line:84%
used to be over 90% in terms
of his trendcasting-- future

00:52:40.640 --> 00:52:41.140 align:middle line:90%
trends.

00:52:41.140 --> 00:52:44.300 align:middle line:84%
And he usually goes a year
to two and even more out.

00:52:44.300 --> 00:52:47.840 align:middle line:84%
And he's saying
this is the future.

00:52:47.840 --> 00:52:48.770 align:middle line:90%
This is the future.

00:52:48.770 --> 00:52:51.030 align:middle line:84%
The old school way
is going to be dying,

00:52:51.030 --> 00:52:52.810 align:middle line:84%
and it is all
going to go online.

00:52:52.810 --> 00:52:54.930 align:middle line:84%
Ultimately, it's going
to be driven online.

00:52:54.930 --> 00:52:56.100 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, and let's
just think about this,

00:52:56.100 --> 00:52:57.649 align:middle line:84%
because a lot of
teachers, I said it,

00:52:57.649 --> 00:52:58.690 align:middle line:90%
are the most traditional.

00:52:58.690 --> 00:53:02.400 align:middle line:84%
My Ph.D. research was about
the adoption of technology.

00:53:02.400 --> 00:53:03.410 align:middle line:90%
But what's happening?

00:53:03.410 --> 00:53:05.490 align:middle line:84%
These huge buildings on
campuses that they're

00:53:05.490 --> 00:53:08.550 align:middle line:84%
paying enormous
utility bills for,

00:53:08.550 --> 00:53:11.010 align:middle line:84%
and people have to take
all the time to drive,

00:53:11.010 --> 00:53:12.744 align:middle line:84%
to park, get ready,
not in that order,

00:53:12.744 --> 00:53:13.910 align:middle line:90%
and end up in the classroom.

00:53:13.910 --> 00:53:14.770 align:middle line:84%
By the time they get
there, they're like,

00:53:14.770 --> 00:53:15.603 align:middle line:90%
you're at the front.

00:53:15.603 --> 00:53:16.295 align:middle line:90%
Teach me.

00:53:16.295 --> 00:53:18.920 align:middle line:84%
They're exhausted by
the time they get there.

00:53:18.920 --> 00:53:22.210 align:middle line:84%
And so a lot of institutions
are going to online classes.

00:53:22.210 --> 00:53:23.910 align:middle line:90%
But they're uploaded paper.

00:53:23.910 --> 00:53:25.730 align:middle line:90%
It's not interactivity.

00:53:25.730 --> 00:53:28.116 align:middle line:84%
They don't understand the
system of how to make it work.

00:53:28.116 --> 00:53:29.240 align:middle line:90%
Perhaps it's a lot of work.

00:53:29.240 --> 00:53:30.790 align:middle line:90%
Perhaps it's a vision.

00:53:30.790 --> 00:53:33.724 align:middle line:84%
But even professors can learn
how to make this happen.

00:53:33.724 --> 00:53:34.390 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Mm-hm.

00:53:34.390 --> 00:53:36.220 align:middle line:84%
And also, you're talking
about some economics,

00:53:36.220 --> 00:53:37.511 align:middle line:90%
which I said we would get into.

00:53:37.511 --> 00:53:41.440 align:middle line:84%
First of all, universities spend
astronomical amounts of money

00:53:41.440 --> 00:53:43.360 align:middle line:84%
to try to doll the
place up and have

00:53:43.360 --> 00:53:46.850 align:middle line:84%
great gyms and amenities
and such to draw

00:53:46.850 --> 00:53:48.840 align:middle line:84%
some new students
in that have parents

00:53:48.840 --> 00:53:50.420 align:middle line:90%
that have a little bit of cash.

00:53:50.420 --> 00:53:52.450 align:middle line:84%
And so here, you're
talking about something

00:53:52.450 --> 00:53:54.010 align:middle line:90%
that's surely about impression.

00:53:54.010 --> 00:53:56.330 align:middle line:84%
It's not even used
toward education.

00:53:56.330 --> 00:53:59.680 align:middle line:84%
Massive amounts of the money
in the total educational system

00:53:59.680 --> 00:54:01.380 align:middle line:84%
in higher education
are going just

00:54:01.380 --> 00:54:03.860 align:middle line:84%
for these impression
factors alone.

00:54:03.860 --> 00:54:05.946 align:middle line:84%
Let's talk about
college tuition.

00:54:05.946 --> 00:54:06.445 align:middle line:90%
The burden.

00:54:06.445 --> 00:54:07.970 align:middle line:84%
We only have a
couple minutes left.

00:54:07.970 --> 00:54:10.650 align:middle line:84%
The burden that kids come
out with now, average,

00:54:10.650 --> 00:54:12.182 align:middle line:84%
on average, compared
to-- and then

00:54:12.182 --> 00:54:14.640 align:middle line:84%
give us an idea of what it
costs to take a course with you.

00:54:14.640 --> 00:54:18.110 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: Well, to me,
the problem is interest.

00:54:18.110 --> 00:54:19.110 align:middle line:90%
Compounded interest.

00:54:19.110 --> 00:54:20.075 align:middle line:90%
Years of interest.

00:54:20.075 --> 00:54:20.690 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes, years.

00:54:20.690 --> 00:54:21.273 align:middle line:90%
>>BOULTER: OK.

00:54:21.273 --> 00:54:23.730 align:middle line:84%
And so you're not just
paying the fee, which

00:54:23.730 --> 00:54:26.640 align:middle line:84%
is already astronomical,
but there's

00:54:26.640 --> 00:54:29.980 align:middle line:84%
government ways that they make
the fees go up and up and up.

00:54:29.980 --> 00:54:32.590 align:middle line:84%
And so I just want to mention
that at the University

00:54:32.590 --> 00:54:34.677 align:middle line:84%
of Calgary, my courses,
when students came

00:54:34.677 --> 00:54:37.010 align:middle line:84%
to me in the Graduate Division
of Educational Research--

00:54:37.010 --> 00:54:39.027 align:middle line:90%
the courses were $1,111.

00:54:39.027 --> 00:54:41.610 align:middle line:84%
But if they took a face to face
class, it was half that price.

00:54:41.610 --> 00:54:42.225 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:54:42.225 --> 00:54:44.350 align:middle line:84%
Because the government
would meet dollar for dollar

00:54:44.350 --> 00:54:45.687 align:middle line:90%
on a face to face class.

00:54:45.687 --> 00:54:47.145 align:middle line:84%
They wanted every
single person who

00:54:47.145 --> 00:54:48.870 align:middle line:84%
was graduating with
a teaching degree

00:54:48.870 --> 00:54:53.130 align:middle line:84%
to be able to have computer
skills and online skills,

00:54:53.130 --> 00:54:54.960 align:middle line:84%
but then they charge
people double.

00:54:54.960 --> 00:54:57.280 align:middle line:84%
Even so, people would rather
take the course online,

00:54:57.280 --> 00:54:59.196 align:middle line:84%
because they can do it
at 2:00 in the morning.

00:54:59.196 --> 00:55:01.496 align:middle line:84%
They could do it from
anyplace they were working.

00:55:01.496 --> 00:55:03.370 align:middle line:84%
A lot of my students
were out of the country.

00:55:03.370 --> 00:55:05.430 align:middle line:90%
And then get a Canadian degree.

00:55:05.430 --> 00:55:06.110 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Mm-hm.

00:55:06.110 --> 00:55:07.484 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: And so
I'm going to be

00:55:07.484 --> 00:55:10.720 align:middle line:84%
charging 10% of
that for a course.

00:55:10.720 --> 00:55:12.560 align:middle line:84%
And just because I
think we can do it.

00:55:12.560 --> 00:55:14.100 align:middle line:84%
You can have more
numbers in there.

00:55:14.100 --> 00:55:16.696 align:middle line:84%
But then when it comes time
to assessing your material

00:55:16.696 --> 00:55:19.070 align:middle line:84%
or getting something marked,
then maybe you pay for that.

00:55:19.070 --> 00:55:21.361 align:middle line:84%
If you need supervision on
a dissertation or something,

00:55:21.361 --> 00:55:22.190 align:middle line:90%
you pay for that.

00:55:22.190 --> 00:55:24.852 align:middle line:84%
But if you're paying
$8,000 a semester or more--

00:55:24.852 --> 00:55:25.810 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Or more yeah.

00:55:25.810 --> 00:55:27.740 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: And the
professor never answers you,

00:55:27.740 --> 00:55:29.870 align:middle line:84%
never answers your phone calls,
doesn't answer your emails,

00:55:29.870 --> 00:55:31.040 align:middle line:90%
what's the $8,000 for?

00:55:31.040 --> 00:55:33.420 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, and if
you're doing that on a loan,

00:55:33.420 --> 00:55:37.060 align:middle line:84%
you're looking at coming out
with $40,000 or $50,000 minimum

00:55:37.060 --> 00:55:38.790 align:middle line:90%
just for a really basic.

00:55:38.790 --> 00:55:40.760 align:middle line:84%
And you're talking
well over $100,000

00:55:40.760 --> 00:55:42.849 align:middle line:84%
if you're going to
any advanced degree.

00:55:42.849 --> 00:55:44.390 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: And how
about a $200 book?

00:55:44.390 --> 00:55:45.100 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, a $200 book.

00:55:45.100 --> 00:55:46.475 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: How
many times can you

00:55:46.475 --> 00:55:49.440 align:middle line:84%
click $1.99 for this,
$2.99, $0.99 for this.

00:55:49.440 --> 00:55:51.315 align:middle line:84%
That takes you a long
time to add up to $200,

00:55:51.315 --> 00:55:52.890 align:middle line:84%
and you're getting
something that's

00:55:52.890 --> 00:55:55.020 align:middle line:84%
fresh and live and
really researched.

00:55:55.020 --> 00:55:57.360 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So essentially,
you don't come out saddled,

00:55:57.360 --> 00:56:01.409 align:middle line:84%
at the age of 23 years old, with
this massive debt on your back

00:56:01.409 --> 00:56:03.200 align:middle line:84%
which already has you
behind the eight ball

00:56:03.200 --> 00:56:05.230 align:middle line:84%
before you ever have a
chance to go prove yourself.

00:56:05.230 --> 00:56:06.350 align:middle line:90%
>>BOULTER: How about this?

00:56:06.350 --> 00:56:08.010 align:middle line:84%
The student can
actually publish,

00:56:08.010 --> 00:56:09.102 align:middle line:90%
and they get the $0.99.

00:56:09.102 --> 00:56:10.060 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: There you go.

00:56:10.060 --> 00:56:12.332 align:middle line:84%
>>BOULTER: And so they're
getting a credit account

00:56:12.332 --> 00:56:13.540 align:middle line:90%
